{
  "texts": [
    "Here, TinyLLM, when trained with only 12.5% of the available training data, not only meets but often exceeds the performance levels achieved by Distill-step-by-step when utilizing the full training set.",
    "This significant reduction in required training data, without sacrificing performance, underscores the practical advantages of TinyLLM, particularly in scenarios where data is scarce or expensive to obtain.This finding holds across different model sizes, including both 80M and 250M parameter student models.",
    "The consistent outstanding performance of TinyLLM in these cases suggests that our method is highly effective in transferring knowledge efficiently, making it a versatile tool for various applications, regardless of the model size.",
    "The capability of achieving superior performance with limited data can be particularly beneficial in resource-constrained environments, where computational resources and training time are restricted.",
    "Outperforming Full Fine-Tuning."
  ]
}